n style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">We would propose that all unsealed Byways Open to All Traffic and all unsealed Unclassified County Roads should be recognised as not being part of the ordinary roads network, and should be reclassified as Restricted Byways.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">In addition we would like to propose that when a local authority declines to impose a traffic regulation order that is widely supported by the public, there should be a right of appeal, either to a magistrate or an independent inspector.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">We have been members of the Yorkshire Green Lanes Alliance since its formation.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">1 September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>